    "zh": "未來感"
  },
  "desc": {
    "en": "Two contrasting colours from opposite sides, leaving a dark seam down the middle. The sense of form comes from where the colours meet, not from brightness.",
    "zh": "用兩個對比色從左右對打，中間留下一條暗部。角色的立體感來自兩色的交界，而不是亮度差。"
  },
  "tip": {
    "en": "Warm against cool gives the strongest contrast. Making the two sides deliberately uneven holds the eye better than an even split.",
    "zh": "冷暖對比最強烈；兩側強度刻意做得不對稱，畫面會比左右平均更耐看。"
  },
